uemacs
=======

A Rust port of MicroEMACS (https://github.com/torvalds/uemacs).

Run:    em [filename]
Build:  cargo build --release 
Test:   cargo test --release


Notation
========

C-x     hold Control and press x
M-x     press Esc then x  (or hold Meta/Alt and press x)
SPC     space bar
RET     return / enter
DEL     backspace


Cursor motion
=============

C-f     forward-char            move one character right
C-b     backward-char           move one character left
C-n     forward-line            next line
C-p     backward-line           previous line
C-a     beginning-of-line
C-e     end-of-line
M-f     forward-word            next word
M-b     backward-word           previous word
M-<     beginning-of-buffer
M->     end-of-buffer
M-g     goto-line               prompt for a line number
C-v     next-page               page down
M-v     previous-page           page up
C-z     backward-page           page up (alt)
M-n     next-paragraph
M-p     previous-paragraph
M-C-f   goto-matching-fence     jump to matching () [] {}


Mark and region
===============

C-SPC   set-mark
M-SPC   set-mark                (alt)
M-.     set-mark                (alt)
C-x C-x exchange-point-and-mark
C-w     kill-region             cut region to kill buffer
M-w     copy-region             copy region to kill buffer
C-y     yank                    paste kill buffer
C-x C-l lower-region
C-x C-u upper-region
M-l     lower-word
M-u     upper-word
M-c     cap-word
M-d     delete-next-word
M-h     delete-previous-word
M-DEL   delete-previous-word    (alt)


Insertion and deletion
======================

self    insert that character at dot
C-d     delete-next-character
C-h     delete-previous-character
DEL     delete-previous-character
C-c     insert-space            insert SPC at dot, dot stays put
C-i     insert-tab              tab
TAB     insert-tab              (alt)
RET     insert-newline
C-m     insert-newline          (alt)
C-j     newline-and-indent      newline + match previous indent
C-o     open-line               like RET but dot stays on this line
C-q     quote-char              insert the next literal byte
C-x q   quote-char              (alt)
C-k     kill-text               kill to end of line (or whole line)
C-t     transpose-characters
C-_     undo


Search and replace
==================

C-s     incremental-search             type pattern to find as you go
C-r     reverse-incremental-search
M-s     search-forward                 use the last pattern, no prompt
M-r     replace-string                 plain replace
M-%     query-replace                  prompt at every match
M-C-r   query-replace                  (alt)
M-m     toggle-magic                   regex on/off for searches

Inside an isearch:
  any character    extends the search pattern
  C-s              find next forward match
  C-r              find next backward match
  DEL              walk back one keystroke of pattern
  C-g / Esc        cancel; dot returns to where you started
  RET              accept; dot stays at the match


Files
=====

C-x C-f find-file               read a file into the current buffer
C-x C-r read-file               replace current buffer with file
C-x C-i insert-file             insert file at dot
C-x C-v view-file               read file in read-only mode
C-x C-s save-file               write to the buffer's filename
C-x C-d save-file               (alt)
C-x C-w write-file              write to a new filename, switch to it
C-x N   change-file-name        set the filename without writing
M-e     set-encryption-key      set the buffer's MDCRYPT key


Buffers
=======

C-x b   switch-buffer
C-x x   next-buffer
C-x k   kill-buffer
C-x C-b list-buffers            show buffer table in *List*
C-x =   buffer-position         line N/M, column, byte position, %
M-C-n   name-buffer             rename current buffer
M-~     unmark-buffer           clear modified flag


Windows
=======

C-x 2   split-window
C-x 1   one-window              keep only the current window
C-x 0   delete-window
C-x o   other-window            next window in cycle
C-x p   previous-window
C-x ^   grow-window
C-x z   grow-window             (alt)
C-x C-z shrink-window
C-x C-n move-window-down
C-x C-p move-window-up
M-C-v   scroll-next-down
M-C-z   scroll-next-up
C-x w   resize-window
M-!     redraw-display          recenter dot vertically
M-C-l   redraw-display          (alt)
C-l     refresh-screen          force complete repaint


Lines and paragraphs
====================

C-x C-a detab-line              tabs -> spaces
C-x C-e entab-line              runs of spaces -> tabs
C-x C-t trim-line               drop trailing whitespace
C-x C-o delete-blank-lines
M-q     fill-paragraph          reflow to fill column
M-j     justify-paragraph       reflow, keep left margin
M-C-w   kill-paragraph
M-C-c   count-words             count in region or buffer


Modes
=====

C-x m   add-mode                add a mode flag to current buffer
C-x C-m delete-mode
M-m     add-global-mode         same, but for every new buffer
M-C-m   delete-global-mode

Mode names accepted by add-mode and delete-mode (case-insensitive):
  WRAP    auto wrap when past fill column
  CMODE   auto-indent for C-like syntax
  SPELL   spell-error parsing flag
  EXACT   case-sensitive search
  VIEW    read-only buffer
  OVER    overwrite mode
  MAGIC   regex search
  CRYPT   encrypt on save
  ASAVE   auto-save


Macros
======

C-x (   start-kbd-macro
C-x )   end-kbd-macro
C-x e   execute-macro           replay the last kbd macro

A "stored macro" lives in a *N* buffer:
  M-x store-macro          name the macro slot 1..9
  M-x execute-macro-1..9   run one of the slots
M-x store-procedure        store keystrokes in *name* buffer
M-x execute-procedure name run *name* as a script
M-x run                    alias for execute-procedure


Help and discovery
==================

M-?     help                    show this list inside uemacs
M-x apropos                     list commands whose name matches
M-a     apropos                 (alt)
C-x ?   describe-key            press a key, see what it runs
M-x describe-bindings           list every binding
M-x bind-to-key                 bind a key to a command
M-k     bind-to-key             (alt)
M-x unbind-key
M-C-k   unbind-key              (alt)


Prefix arguments
================

C-u     universal-argument      default 4; press again to multiply by 4
                                or follow with digits, e.g. C-u 1 0 C-f
                                = forward 10 chars
M-<n>   numeric argument        same effect, e.g. M-5 C-f


Quitting
========

C-g     keyboard-quit / abort-command
C-x C-c exit-emacs              prompt if there are unsaved buffers
M-z     quick-exit              save all dirty buffers and exit
C-z     not quit; this is backward-page (uemacs convention)


Shell and subprocess
====================

C-x C   i-shell                 spawn an interactive subshell
C-x D   suspend-emacs           SIGTSTP back to the shell
C-x !   shell-command           one-shot shell command
C-x $   execute-program         run a program
C-x #   filter-buffer           pipe buffer through external command
C-x @   pipe-command            replace buffer with command output


Editor variables ($name in macro language)
==========================================

$tab       tab width                  $fillcol   fill column
$scroll    page scroll amount         $gmode     global mode bits
$search    last search pattern        $replace   last replacement
$match     last matched text          $kill      kill buffer contents
$curline   current line number        $curcol    current column
$curchar   character under dot        $bufname   current buffer name
$fname     buffer's filename          $version   editor version
$progname  "uemacs"                  $lastkey   last keystroke
$asave / $acount  auto-save params
$cmode / $lwidth / $wline / $cwline / $line  buffer geometry
$status / $discmd / $disinp / $rval / $target / $ram
$flicker / $sres / $debug / $palette / $seed / $tpause / $pending
$gflags / $overlap / $pagelen / $curwidth

Function-like builtins available as &name(args):
  &add &sub &mul &div &mod &neg &abs
  &equ &les &gre &sle &sgr &seq
  &and &or &not &band &bor &bxo &ban &bno
  &len &cat &lef &rig &mid &sin &upp &low
  &asc &chr &xla &ind &env &fin &gtk &exi
  &tru &rnd &bin

